<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 27 at 6:48PM CST  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT CENTRAL RHEA...NORTHWESTERN
BRADLEY...MEIGS...CENTRAL MCMINN AND HAMILTON COUNTIES THROUGH 845 PM
EST...
At 748 PM EST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Harrison, or 7 miles northeast of Chattanooga, moving northeast at 50
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Chattanooga, Athens, Dayton, Decatur, Soddy-Daisy, Signal Mountain,
Spring City, Walden, Lakesite, and Ridgeside.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
